</p><hr>
<p><strong>Trapezoid&nbsp;</strong>or <strong>trapezium</strong>, as it's k=
nown in the UK,&nbsp; is a quadrilateral with two parallel sides, shown as =
the top and bottom in this diagram.&nbsp; The height of a trapezoid (h) is =
the perpendicular distance between the two parallel sides.</p>

<p>A trapezoid volume is made of four trapezoids one the sides.</p>

